      "fullText": "

The Mission

To build the first trusted platform for verified homes, movers, and handyman services in Nigeria—creating a rental experience that is transparent, efficient, and stress-free from start to finish.

The Context

There is no "rental platform" in Nigeria. Not really.

What exists are classifieds. Notice boards. WhatsApp groups where scammers roam free. Property listings with no verification, no accountability, and no follow-through.

And for movers and handymen? There's nothing at all. Just word of mouth, street corner posters, and the hope that the person you called won't overcharge or disappear.

This isn't a market. It's a gap.

The Opportunity

The first company to earn trust in this chaos wins everything.

Primer will be that company.


Step 1: Build trust where it doesn't exist.

In a market with no standards, we set them.

We start in one high-density urban area—students, young professionals, people who need homes and services right now. And we do what no one else is doing:

· Properties: We visit every home ourselves. Meet every landlord. Photograph every room. We don't aggregate listings—we create them from scratch.
· Movers: We vet, interview, and test every moving company. Reliability. Pricing transparency. Care with belongings.
· Handymen: We verify skills, background, and pricing. No more "he came, quoted double, and left."

What emerges is the first curated, trustworthy set of rental services in Nigeria.

Why start here? Because in a market with no trust, the first mover who builds it owns the category. We're not entering a market. We're creating one.


Step 2: Scale through technology and operations.

Once the manual model works in one location, we systematize it.

· Expand cities: Lagos. Abuja. Port Harcourt. Ibadan. Everywhere the chaos exists.
· Expand services: Properties, movers, repairs, handymen—the full rental lifecycle.
· Build the platform: Verification workflows, payments, contracts, service requests, ratings.

But here's what makes Primer different: we don't become a "listing site." We become the operating system for renting.

· Tenants find verified homes, book verified movers, and request verified repairs—all in one place.
· Landlords get reliable tenants, vetted service providers, and tools to manage their properties.
· Service providers get consistent work, transparent payments, and reputations they can build.

Why? Because a market doesn't exist until someone builds the infrastructure. We're building it.


Step 3: Become the infrastructure of Nigerian renting.

When thousands of Nigerians use Primer to find homes, move, and maintain their apartments, we own something unprecedented:

The first trusted rental ecosystem in the country.

· Digital Tenant Identity: A portable profile with verified rental history. Landlords stop demanding "2 years upfront" because they trust Primer-verified tenants.
· Landlord OS: The first software built for Nigerian property owners. Tenant screening. Maintenance tracking. Legal docs. All in one place.
· Service Provider Network: The largest, most reliable network of vetted movers and handymen in the country. When something breaks, Nigerians open Primer.
· The Nigerian Rental Registry: The first accurate dataset on housing, prices, ownership, and scams. This data will inform policy, enable banking products, and create transparency where none existed.

Why? Because the first mover who builds trust doesn't just win a market—they define it. Primer will be the name Nigerians trust for renting.


The Reality

We are first. That means:

· Step 1 will be manual. Slow. Unsexy. We will verify every property and every service provider ourselves because no one else has.
· Step 2 will require operational excellence. Scaling trust is harder than scaling code.
· Step 3 is years away. But if we execute Steps 1 and 2 with integrity, no one can follow us there.

We're not building for quick growth. We're building the foundation of rental trust in Nigeria.

From scratch.

Join Us

If you want to build something that doesn't exist yet:

· Verifiers who can hit the streets, meet landlords, and inspect properties.
· Engineers who want to build the first real rental platform in Nigeria.
· Service providers—movers, handymen, repair experts—who want to be part of the first trusted network.
· Believers who understand that first movers who build trust win everything.

Primer is the first step.

Let's build the market."
